article.headline: Villanova outlasts William & Mary 35-31
article.story: WILLIAMSBURG, Va. -- John Robertson threw for 267 yards and two touchdowns, including a 13-yard strike to Kevin Gulyas with 52 seconds left, to lead Villanova to a 35-31 win over William & Mary on Saturday. Trailing 31-28 with 2:01 remaining in the game, Robertson led the Wildcats on a 7-play, 69-yard drive, capped off by the touchdown to Gulyas. Robertson added 63 yards rushing and two touchdowns, while Clay Horne finished with 84 yards receiving for Villanova (6-1, 4-0 Colonial). Steve Cluley threw for 350 yards and had three touchdowns passes for the Williams & Mary (4-3, 1-2). Tre McBride finished with 11 catches for 209 yards and two scores to lead the Tribe. Cluley's 3-yard pass to Andrew Caskin gave William & Mary a 31-28 lead with 10:23 left in the fourth. The win was Villanova's sixth straight since its double overtime loss to Syracuse in week one.
